We explore patterns of DVM in zooplankton using a generic predator–prey model with structured prey: in our model, the prey is zooplankton and the predator is planktivorous fish. For simplicity, we only include two stages of zooplankton which we refer to as adults and juveniles and use the same model structure as in Kuzenkov and Kuzenkova (2012), Morozov and Kuzenkov (2016). The model can be easily extended by including more developmental stages of herbivorous zooplankton. The model equations read12At(v,t)=p(v)J(v,t)-s(v)A(v,t)-ϕ1A(v,t)I(t)-fA(v)A(v,t)F(v,t),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
